The paper discusses the training of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of Cyclical Learning Rates (CLR) and linear network interpolation suggests that the paper is likely to be related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The exploration of loss function topology and the examination of the nature of neural networks suggest that the paper may also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
